🔹 1. FILTERS in Power BI (Step by Step)
Filters control what data is shown in visuals, pages, or the entire report.
👉 Types of Filters
Filter Type	Works On
Visual Level	Only one chart
Page Level	All charts in one page
Report Level	Entire report
✅ Steps to Apply Filters
1.	Open Power BI Desktop
2.	Load your data (Home → Get Data → Excel)
3.	Create any visual (e.g., Bar chart)
4.	On the right side, you will see Filters pane
▶ Visual Level Filter
5.	Click the chart
6.	In Filters pane → drag a field (e.g., Category)
7.	Choose values you want (tick/untick)
➡ Only that chart changes.
▶ Page Level Filter
8.	In Filters pane → under Page level filters
9.	Drag a field (e.g., Region)
10.	Select values
➡ All visuals on this page change.
▶ Report Level Filter
11.	Under Report level filters
12.	Drag field (e.g., Year)
13.	Select values
➡ Entire report changes.
 
 

